      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CARRAMAR RAVEN (1) hit the ground running with a slick early sectional but had to settle for a minor placing when a half a length second over 300m at this track, clocking 17.08. Good form should continue. TEA ROSE (6) was well back throughout but attacked the line strongly to place, 3 lengths from the winner (19.93) at Capalaba in Restricted WIN. Nicely placed to grab a well-deserved win. SAUSAGE GAMBLER (7) three runs back produced a sharp 27.74 win over 484m at this track then has found the minor money in two runs since. Has the ability and looks a key chance. BONALL RETURNS (8) proved himself from this box last start so worth keeping in mind.",
